---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Contribute — how to talk to robots"
  description="Submit a prompt or guide to the community library. How to Talk to Robots is open source and community-built."
>
  <article class="prose section">
    <h1>Contribute</h1>
    <p>
      This library is community-built. If you've found a way to use AI that made
      your work or life genuinely easier, someone else needs it too.
    </p>
    <h2>Two ways to send it in</h2>
    <h3>The easy way</h3>
    <p>
      <a href="/contact/">Send us your prompt or idea</a> with a sentence or two
      about when you use it. We'll edit it into the library format and credit you.
    </p>
    <h3>The open-source way</h3>
    <p>
      Every library entry is a markdown file in
      <a href="https://github.com/thirdspaced/talktorobots">the public repository</a>.
      Open a pull request adding a file to <code>src/content/library/</code> —
      the template in the repo shows the format.
    </p>
    <h2>What makes a good entry</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Titled as the question someone would actually ask ("How do I use AI to…")</li>
      <li>A copy-paste prompt that asks the person questions, not just a command</li>
      <li>A few sentences on when to use it and what to watch out for</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</Base>
